A compilation of the bugs we found after we conducted testing throughout Week 1 to Week 4.

Some potential bugs may appear in the Zenzone Study Buddy system. 
The study tracking feature may have problems. 
For example, the system might record the wrong amount of study time or fail to save the user's study progress. 
The daily study check-in feature could also have bugs, such as the check-in button not responding or the system not recording the user's daily check-in.
In some cases, the app might mark a student as absent even though they already checked in for their study session.
Customers may feel dissatisﬁed if the app does not work smoothly or does not help them manage their study time.
For example, if the tracking feature, and daily study check-in does not work properly, students may feel frustrated.
Some students may also be unhappy if their daily check-in is not recorded because they may lose their study streak or progress.
A confusing interface may also make it difficult for users to check in or view their study history.
If the system records incorrect study time or fails to track daily study activity, users may not trust the app and may choose to use other study tools instead.

